LAUNCHING APPIMAGE
sudo apt-get install fuse
sudo gpasswd -a YOUR_NAME fuse (if needed)
Make sure your GLIBC version is at least 2.15. You can run ldd --version to verify this.
sudo chown $USER *.AppImage (if needed)
chmod +x *.AppImage
If you have a SSL: CERTIFICATE_VERIFY_FAILED error, do the following:
sudo apt-get install slocate ca-certificates
(check that /usr/sbin is in `echo $PATH`
if it is not:
export PATH=\/usr\/sbin\:$PATH)
updatedb
locate ca-bundle.crt
Get the path that locate provides and do `export SSL_CERT_FILE=YOUR_PATH`. You can save it in your .bashrc.

MANUALLY SETTING UP PYTHON
# Should be installed by default
sudo apt-get install python3 zlib1g libjpeg8 python3-tk appstream-util curl
# Package names will differ, see https://pillow.readthedocs.io/en/latest/installation.html
sudo apt-get install libtiff5-dev libjpeg62-turbo-dev zlib1g-dev libfreetype6-dev liblcms2-dev libwebp-dev libharfbuzz-dev libfribidi-dev tcl8.6-dev tk8.6-dev
sudo pip3 install pafy httplib2 Pillow google-api-python-client oauth2client google configparser youtube-dl
